SIMPLE: anxious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anxious
<hw>Anx"ious</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧k"sh⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>anxius</ets>, fr. <ets>angere</ets> to cause pain, choke;
akin to Gr. <grk>'a`gchein</grk> to choke. See <er>Anger</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of anxiety or disquietude; greatly concerned or
solicitous, esp. respecting something future or unknown; being in
painful suspense; -- applied to persons; <as>as, <ex>anxious</ex> for
the issue of a battle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Accompanied with, or causing, anxiety; worrying; --
applied to things; <as>as, <ex>anxious</ex> labor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sweet of life, from which⟦br⟧
God hath bid dwell far off all <qex>anxious</qex> cares.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Earnestly desirous; <as>as, <ex>anxious</ex> to
please</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He sneers alike at those who are <qex>anxious</qex> to preserve
and at those who are eager for reform.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note><xex>Anxious</xex> is followed by <it>for</it>, <it>about</it>,
<it>concerning</it>, etc., before the object of solicitude.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Solicitous; careful; uneasy; unquiet; restless;
concerned; disturbed; watchful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anxiously</ent>⟦br⟧
